ent, worktree support, and skills framework for extending beyond code generation.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-03-04\",\n    \"category\": \"AI coding CLI/Agent\",\n    \"sources\": [\"OpenAI\", \"The New Stack\", \"TechRadar\", \"Engadget\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Native Windows agent sandbox open-sourced on GitHub\",\n      \"Multi-agent coding with coordinated teams\",\n      \"Skills for Figma, Linear, Cloudflare, Netlify, Vercel\",\n      \"No Mac required to use Codex\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"VS Code 1.111 Autopilot\",\n    \"url\": \"https://code.visualstudio.com/updates/v1_111\",\n    \"description\": \"VS Code's first autonomous AI agent mode (Autopilot) that allows AI to work independently until task completion, with new permissions controls for agent autonomy. Switched VS Code to weekly release cadence.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-03-09\",\n    \"category\": \"AI IDE integration\",\n    \"sources\": [\"Microsoft\", \"The Register\", \"Visual Studio Magazine\", \"Dev.to\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"First autonomous AI agent mode in VS Code\",\n      \"All new features in version 1.111 are AI-related\",\n      \"Users can control how much autonomy an AI agent has during sessions\",\n      \"Also referred to as 'YOLO mode' because it auto-accepts everything\",\n      \"Some developers find it 'scary' due to the autonomous nature\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"AutoResearch\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/karpathy/autoresearch\",\n    \"description\": \"An autonomous AI research lab that runs on a single GPU, allowing AI agents to run hundreds of experiments overnight and self-improve through iteration. Released by Andrej Karpathy with just 630 lines of Python code.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-03-07\",\n    \"category\": \"AI coding agent\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub\", \"X/Twitter\", \"Hacker News\", \"LinkedIn\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"10,000+ GitHub stars within days of release\",\n      \"A tiny but complete AI research lab\",\n      \"The agent modifies training scripts and iterates on improvements autonomously\",\n      \"AI self-evolving software capabilities\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"cicaddy\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/redhat-developer/cicaddy\",\n    \"description\": \"A Python-based pipeline AI agent framework that runs AI-driven tasks inside CI/CD pipeline jobs with multi-LLM support (Gemini, OpenAI, Claude), MCP tool integration, and DSPy-based task definitions for agentic workflows.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-03-12\",\n    \"category\": \"Workflow orchestration agent\",\n    \"sources\": [\"Red Hat Developers\", \"GitHub\", \"Dev.to\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"CI as an agentic runtime - no separate platform needed\",\n      \"One-shot execution with multi-turn reasoning\",\n      \"Security through containerization\",\n      \"Your CI system is the scheduler, executor, and audit trail\"\n    ]\n  }\n]",
